Author:  SOR
Vol / Page:  42
Edition:
Quote:  <i>SHARK, SCHOOL </i>(a) Scientific name: <i>Galeorhinus australis</i> (principally). (b) Suggested commercial name[s]: Flake Fillets. (c) Other common names: B.B., Big Boys; Soupfin; Grey Boys; Tope or Topi.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Fisherman's Bible
Author:  WILSON
Vol / Page:  224
Edition:
Quote:  SCHOOLFISH The flesh, like that of the gummies, is quite edible and regularly marketed, usually as Lemonfish. The Schoolshark is usually dark-grey-green above and white below. Known also as Tope and Sand shark they are the only fish who close their eyes when they sleep.
Notes:

